o return south.{{sfn|Monaghan|1984|pp=185\u2013194}}  The victory at Dry Wood Creek had allowed Price to be able to continue his northward expedition.{{sfn|Castel|1968|p=50}}\n\nToday, the site of the battle is commemorated with a series of markers near [[Deerfield, Missouri]].  A museum in nearby [[Nevada, Missouri]] provides coverage of both the Battle of Dry Wood Creek and the American Civil War in Missouri as a whole.{{sfn|Weeks|2009|p=42}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==References==\n*{{cite book |last=Castel |first=Albert |title=General Sterling Price and the Civil War in the West |date=1968 |publisher=Louisiana State University Press |location=Baton Rouge, Louisiana |isbn=0-8071-1854-0 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Gerteis |first1=Louis S. |title=The Civil War in Missouri |date=2012 |publisher=University of Missouri Press |location=Columbia, Missouri |isbn=978-0-8262-1972-5 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last=Kennedy |first=Frances |title=The Civil War Battlefield Guide |date=1998 |edition=2nd |publisher=Houghton Mifflin |location=Boston/New York |isbn=978-0-395-74012-5|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Monaghan |first1=Jay |title=Civil War on the Western Border, 1854{{endash}}1865 |date=1984 |publisher=University of Nebraska Press |location=Lincoln, Nebraska |isbn=978-0-8032-8126-4 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Weeks |first1=Michael |title=The Complete Civil War Road Trip Guide |date=2009 |publisher=The Countryman Press |location=Woodstock, Vermont |isbn=978-0-88150-860-4 |ref=harv}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20041119074750/http://www.griffingweb.com/captain_creitz%27s_diary.htm Diary of a Union cavalryman present at Dry Wood Creek]\n\n{{Missouri in the Civil War}}\n\n{{Coord|37.8197|-94.4862|display=title|region:US-MO_type:event}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dry Wood Creek}}\n[[Category:Operations to Control Missouri|Dry Wood Creek]]\n[[Category:Battles of the Trans-Mississippi Theater of the American Civil War|Dry 